  "texts": [
    "Consequently, they are unable to replicate the experience of tradetional learning (Dwivedi et al., 2022).",
    "Supporting this, it is found that virtual technologies such as virtual reality (VR), augmented reality (AR), extended reality (XR), and mixed reality (MR), do not, on their own, guarantee positive learning results (Marks & Thomas, 2022; Tegoan et al., 2021) due to issues related to the multisensory experiences of students in terms of teaching content quality and the appropriateness of realistic dynamic interactions.",
    "Therefore, the utilization of metaverse technology in education has the ability to enhance the online learning experience and make it simpler for educational service providers to establish virtual classrooms that imitate traditional classrooms (Teng et al., 2022).",
    "COVID-19 disrupted education and highlighted the importance of replicating in-person learning (Kim et al., 2022; Pappas & Giannakos, 2021).",
    "These acquired insights expedite educational reform and improve educational system readiness."
  ]
}